  "description": [
    "WOMENS COUNCIL COMMENDS HOOVER Indorses Presidents Stand on Law Enforcement and World Peace Presentation to President Hoover of ft resolution indorsing his stand on law enforcement and world peace by Mrs Luke Johnson of Atlanta Ga was the final action of the Womens Missionary Council of the Methodist Episcopal Church South at its closing session today Mrs Johnson told the President that she represented the women who stood by Bishop Cannon and helped to break the Democratic lines in the recent elec tion President Hoover thanked the council and Mrs Johnson for their con sideration Officers and leaders of the council stayed over after yesterdays concluding session for an executive meeting today to discuss plans and policies of the council for the coming year They will get into shape legislation to be presented at the General Conference of the Meth odist Church in 1930 24 Mission Workers Named Twentyfour new mission workers were consecrated in the service of the Church last night at the closing meet ing of the conference All are woman seniors at Searitt College which is maintained at Nash ville Tcnn by the council Eleven be came deaconesses and 13 were assigned to foreign fields Bishop W"
  ],
